sections.name: Important information to be read by all applicants

fields.label: The ACROD Parking Program aims to support people with a severe walking restriction to access the community.
To be eligible for a disability parking permit, you must meet one of the following criteria:
• You are unable to walk and always require the use of a wheelchair; or
• Your ability to walk is severely restricted by a permanent medical condition or disability; or

groups.label: • Your ability to walk is severely restricted by a temporary medical condition or disability.
If you do not meet at least one of the above criteria, you are not eligible for a disability parking permit. For further information, please contact the ACROD Parking Program on (08) 9242 5544.
• A permit will not automatically be granted. All applications are subject to assessment by the ACROD Parking Program.
• Any person who obtains a disability parking permit by false statement or misrepresentation will have their permit cancelled.
• PART A (pages 1-3) of this form must be completed by the applicant.

• PART B (pages 4-5) of this form must be completed by a Doctor or Occupational Therapist. You may need to book an extended appointment to ensure your Doctor has suf?cient time to complete Part B of this form.
• Place a clear 'X' inside the correct box.
• If you make a mistake, ?ll the entire box and mark the correct box.
Post: Acrod Parking Program, PO Box 184, Northbridge WA 6865
• To request more forms, email app@app.org.au or phone (08) 9242 5544.
T (08) 9242 5544 F (08) 9242 5044 W www.app.org.au E app@app.org.au
Note: A residential address must be provided below.

How often do you use a mobility aid? State number in box below then go to question 4.
3. For those who walk without the assistance of a mobility aid, how often is your walking severely restricted? State number in box below.
4. How far can you walk before you stop or rest?
This question must be answered. To help you measure a distance, the width of one car bay generally equals 2.5 metres.
5. Describe how your body feels when you walk (i.e. what are your symptoms?)
6. Describe how you walk (e.g. speed, balance or how you think you look to others when you walk).

Criteria l: The applicant is unable to walk and always requires the use of a wheelchair; or
Criteria 2: The applicant's ability to walk is severely restricted by a permanent medical condition or disability; or
Criteria 3: The applicant's ability to walk is severely restricted by a temporary medical condition or disability.
• Only applicants that meet the criteria will be provided with a renewable or temporary permit. Temporary permits may be eligible for an extension.
• Applicants with sensory, cognitive, intellectual or psychiactric impairment alone do not meet the criteria unless they also have a severe walking restriction.
• The ACROD Parking Program can advise on eligibility for short-term walking restrictions.
• For further information please request a 'Health Professionals Guide'.
2. State the applicant's primary and secondary diagnoses that impact on their ability to walk. Please indicate the date of each diagnosis.
3. Provide objective measurements indicating the severity of the applicant's condition (e.g. spirometry, echocardiogram, doppler studies).
4. If the applicant uses a walking aid, how long will they need it?
5. Is the applicant's ability to walk likely to improve following treatment, surgery recovery or rehabilitation?
6. What is the expected duration of the treatment, recovery or rehabilitation?
7. Is surgery an option in the future?
? The information supplied within this application form is correct to the best of my knowledge.

? I agree to be contacted to verify the information contained in this form.

field_17_1_0.label: Criteria l: The applicant is unable to walk and always requires the use of a wheelchair; or

field_17_2_0.label: Criteria 2: The applicant's ability to walk is severely restricted by a permanent medical condition or disability; or

field_17_3_0.label: Criteria 3: The applicant's ability to walk is severely restricted by a temporary medical condition or disability.

field_17_4_0.label: • Only applicants that meet the criteria will be provided with a renewable or temporary permit. Temporary permits may be eligible for an extension.

field_17_5_0.label: • Applicants with sensory, cognitive, intellectual or psychiactric impairment alone do not meet the criteria unless they also have a severe walking restriction.

field_17_6_0.label: • The ACROD Parking Program can advise on eligibility for short-term walking restrictions.

field_17_7_0.label: • For further information please request a 'Health Professionals Guide'.
